The paper focuses on a data-intensive machine learning problem and discusses challenges and strategies of unstructured data processing, data formats for storage and efficient access, and graph processing at scale. These topics are relevant to several CS sub-categories, including database systems (cs.DB), natural language processing (cs.CL), distributed and parallel computing (cs.DC), social and information networks (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
